![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/744a1bb9-7ae0-4f89-b334-67795bce7360/20240510_171138.jpg)

Smackdown opens with Cody Rhodes being invited out by Nick Aldis so he can find out who his opponent for the WWE Championship will be in Saudi Arabia

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/fee25bd0-3da4-4e2d-8289-a7348bcad2c4/20240510_171158.jpg)

Champion vs Champion at King and Queen of the Ring. Cody Rhodes vs Logan Paul.

Paul brings up the fact that both he and Cody began their current WWE runs at WrestleMania 38. Paul says this was never Cody's story. It was Paul who put the rocket on WWE's back.

Says he bets a lot of people stand across from Logan Paul and call him a dumbass. But Cody won’t belittle his accomplishments in the ring. Cody wants the US title and Cody wants to become grand slam champion.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/6d9ebc7c-2ce3-4820-adc1-152302318a33/20240510_173744.jpg)

*   ## **_QUEEN OF THE RING ROUND 1: NIA JAX DEF. NAOMI_**
    

This match had a lot more time to develop into something than you would usually see on SmackDown. Very good stuff.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/391a85ec-a28e-4597-bf94-937ccdbf74a2/20240510_175340.jpg)

*   ## **_KING OF THE RING ROUND 1: CARMELO HAYES DEF. BARON CORBIN_**
    

A lot better showing for Melo than his match with Cody. Baron Corbin wasn’t so bad here either.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/0c1440a4-2930-4332-b64e-1a7a8467d140/20240510_181021.jpg)

*   ## **_QUEEN OF THE RING ROUND 1: JADE CARGILL DEF. PIPER NIVEN_**
    

Piper Niven got a lot of offense in on Jade before Jade finally turns it around and wins. Cute moment between Jade and Bianca and they pass each other on our way to the next match.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/8d91455c-4bda-49fb-a36d-90ab6d69eef6/20240510_181935.jpg)

*   ## **_QUEEN OF THE RING ROUND 1: BIANCA BELAIR DEF. CANDICE LERAE_**
    

Little more than a squash match.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/b2c7f630-e48e-4e75-9654-54abf3302801/20240510_182013.jpg)

Solo Sikoa confronts Paul Heyman about Heyman pulling Roman from the draft and causing the Bloodline to get drafted at Round 3 instead of 1.

Solo says he understands that Paul is the Wiseman and he’s just trying to help.

But Solo saw the look Paul was giving to Jey last week. Was he asking for help or something? Has he really not spoken to Roman since Mania?

Well Solo says he’s spoken to Roman. Roman supposedly told Solo is in charge until he returns. Solo pulls Paul in for a hug and says he loves him.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/47089d8f-1652-4b71-b4ed-eb012c7bfdb5/20240510_182957.jpg)

*   ## **_KING OF THE RING ROUND 1: TAMA TONGA DEF. ANGELO DAWKINS_**
    

Pretty quick match that ends when the Bloodline overwhelms the Street Profits.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/651bcd39-b720-4661-9582-c3ef620ec9fa/20240510_185944.jpg)

*   ## **_KING OF THE RING ROUND 1: RANDY ORTON DEF. AJ STYLES_**
    

Another strong match from AJ Styles and Randy Orton. The show closes with Orton moving on to the next round of the KotR.